{
  "texts": [
    "Depending on the availability of structural data, VS/HTS can be conducted using either receptor-based or ligandbased methods [61].",
    "However, in the practical application of anesthetic drug development, the utilization of structure-based methods is more prevalent.",
    "Ligand-based drug designIn cases where structural information about drug targets is not available, ligand-based drug design (LBDD) can be a preferred approach [62].",
    "The principle behind LBDD is that molecules with similar structures tend to share similar biological properties.",
    "Common LBDD methods include quantitative structure-affinity relationship (QSAR), similarity search, and pharmacophore modeling [63]."
  ]
}